# Zaneva AI Content Studio - Technical Specification & PRD

## Project Overview
**Project Name**: Zaneva AI Content Studio  
**Purpose**: Web application to manage multiple ChatGPT Plus and Google AI Pro (Gemini) accounts for automated marketing content creation for Zaneva (Muslimah sportswear brand).  
The app allows users to create reusable **Projects** (product collections), generate high-quality storyboards/images using ChatGPT web UI, then generate short videos (9:16 Reels/Shorts) using Gemini (Veo / Image-to-Video) with smart account rotation.

**Key Goals**:
- Centralize management of 1-3 ChatGPT + 10-15 Gemini accounts
- Support reusable product projects (upload once, use many times)
- Manual trigger for generation steps
- Exhaust one account's quota before rotating to the next
- Track approximate quota usage and reset timers
- Downloadable storyboards and videos
- Easy deployment on EasyPanel with Docker + PostgreSQL

**Target Users**: Admin (Ryan) + small team (affiliate/content team)

---

## Core Features (MVP)

### 1. Account Management
- Add/Edit/Delete ChatGPT accounts and Gemini accounts
- Store **encrypted session cookies** (never store plain password)
- Status per account: Active / Paused / Error
- Manual "Test Login" button
- Display last used time and estimated remaining quota

### 2. Project Management
- Create new Project: Name, Description, 6-8 product images upload, brand guidelines notes
- Edit / Delete Project
- View all Projects in a grid or list
- Each Project stores the uploaded images permanently (saved in storage)

### 3. Content Generation Flow (Manual Trigger)
For each Project:

**Step A: Generate Storyboard / Images**
- User selects Project + chooses starting ChatGPT account (or auto)
- App uses Playwright to open ChatGPT web, logs in with stored session, sends detailed prompt + uploads reference images
- Generates multiple image variations / storyboard panels (consistent with Zaneva branding, hijab, activewear style)
- Saves generated images linked to the Project
- Tracks how many generations done on that account

**Step B: Generate Video**
- User selects generated storyboard image(s)
- App uses Playwright to open Gemini web, logs in, uploads image + detailed motion prompt
- Generates short video (4-8 seconds, 9:16 vertical preferred)
- Saves video file linked to the Project
- Tracks generation count per Gemini account

**Account Rotation Rule**:
- Always try to exhaust current account first (based on tracked usage count)
- When account reaches estimated limit (configurable per account type), automatically switch to next available account
- User can manually force which account to use

### 4. Quota & Monitoring Dashboard
- Per account view: 
  - Estimated remaining capacity (based on generation count + known limits)
  - Last reset time (user can manually mark "Reset" or app estimates based on 3-5 hour pattern for Gemini video)
  - Total generations today / this cycle
- Global dashboard showing all accounts status

### 5. File Management & Download
- All generated storyboards and videos are downloadable
- Option to bulk download per Project
- (Nice to have) One-click upload to specific Google Drive folder

### 6. History & Logs
- Full history of every generation (which project, which account used, timestamp, prompt used, result file)
- Search and filter history

---

## Technical Stack (Recommended)

- **Framework**: Next.js 15 (App Router) – full-stack
- **Database**: PostgreSQL + Prisma ORM
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui
- **File Storage**: Local filesystem (EasyPanel volume) or S3-compatible (MinIO / Cloudflare R2)
- **Background Jobs & Automation**: 
  - Playwright (Chromium with stealth plugins)
  - BullMQ + Redis (for job queue) – or simpler database-based queue for MVP
- **Authentication**: NextAuth.js v5 (or custom JWT for admin-only first)
- **Deployment**: Docker + Docker Compose, deployable on EasyPanel
- **Language**: TypeScript

---

## Database Schema (Prisma)

```prisma
model Account {
  id            String   @id @default(cuid())
  type          String   // "chatgpt" | "gemini"
  name          String
  email         String?
  sessionCookie String?  // encrypted
  status        String   @default("active")
  lastUsedAt    DateTime?
  usageCount    Int      @default(0)
  resetAt       DateTime?
  notes         String?
  createdAt     DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt     DateTime @updatedAt

  generations   Generation[]
}

model Project {
  id          String   @id @default(cuid())
  name        String
  description String?
  brandNotes  String?
  createdAt   DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt   DateTime @updatedAt

  images      ProjectImage[]
  generations Generation[]
}

model ProjectImage {
  id        String  @id @default(cuid())
  projectId String
  url       String  // local path or storage url
  filename  String
  order     Int
  project   Project @relation(fields: [projectId], references: [id], onDelete: Cascade)
}

model Generation {
  id          String   @id @default(cuid())
  projectId   String
  accountId   String
  type        String   // "storyboard" | "video"
  prompt      String   @db.Text
  resultUrl   String?
  status      String   @default("pending") // pending, processing, completed, failed
  error       String?
  createdAt   DateTime @default(now())

  project     Project  @relation(fields: [projectId], references: [id])
  account     Account  @relation(fields: [accountId], references: [id])
}


Key Technical Requirements

Playwright Automation Layer
Use stealth plugins to reduce detection
Support persistent browser context per account (save cookies)
Handle long-running video generation (polling status)
Good error handling + retry logic

Security
Encrypt session cookies at rest (use AES or similar)
Never expose raw cookies to frontend
Admin-only access (at least for MVP)

Job Queue
Every generation request goes through a queue
Status updates in real-time (use Server-Sent Events or polling)
Manual trigger only (no auto scheduling in MVP)

File Handling
Store uploaded product images and generated files
Provide direct download links



Non-Functional Requirements

Easy to deploy on EasyPanel (Docker + docker-compose)
Clear logging for debugging automation issues
Good error messages when Playwright fails (e.g. "Login failed", "Rate limit hit", etc.)
Responsive UI (desktop first, since used internally)


Out of Scope for MVP

Full team collaboration with roles & permissions
Automatic prompt optimization / A/B testing
Direct TikTok Shop / Shopee integration
Advanced analytics


Development Instructions for AI Coder (Grok Build)
Please generate a complete, production-ready starter for this application with the following priorities:

1- Clean, well-structured Next.js 15 + TypeScript + Prisma + Tailwind + shadcn/ui codebase.
2- Complete Prisma schema + migrations.
3- Account management pages (list, add, edit, test login).
4- Project CRUD with image upload (use UploadThing or local storage for MVP).
5- Generation flow UI (select project → trigger storyboard → trigger video).
6- Simple dashboard showing account status and estimated quota.
7- Basic Playwright integration example (even if mocked at first) with clear comments on where to expand automation.
8- Docker + docker-compose.yml ready for EasyPanel deployment (include PostgreSQL + optional Redis).
9- Good README with setup instructions, how to add accounts, and how to run Playwright jobs.

Make the code clean, well-commented, and easy to extend later.
Start by creating the project structure and core pages first.